dependency.description: The photos app allows you to browse JPEG, BMP, PNG and GIF files using the file system folders.
The Podcasting app allows you to subscribe and listen to your favorite podcasts.
The Jabber app allows you to connect to the Jabber messenger service.
The Email app allows you to view your new incoming email on your TiVo.
The Traffic app displays maps of local traffic conditions.
The Movies app allows you view local movie theater listings.
The Videocasting app allows you to subscribe and listen to your favorite videocasts.
The iTunes app allows you to play your iTunes playlists on your TiVo. Only MP3 files are supported.
The music app allows a user to browse MP3 files using the file system folders.
The Playlists app allows you to play your favorite .m3u and .pls playlists.
The Jukebox app allows you to create dynamic playlists.
The Shoutcast app allows you to listen to online radio streams based on your favorite genres.
The menu app groups Galleon apps.
The Internet Slideshows app displays photos from RSS feeds.
The RSS app allows you to view their favorite RSS feeds.

The organizer imports MP3 files from a list of directories, reads their tags and then creates a record for each file in an embedded database. These records are then used to categorize all of the MP3 files based on their tag information.
The weather app displays the current weather conditions, 5 day forecast, local radar image, national radar image and any weather alerts.
The ToGo app allows a user to control the ToGo feature directly from the TiVo recorder instead of using the TiVo desktop software on the PC.
The Desktop app provides a live view of the desktop of the PC running Galleon.
The Internet app allows you to view Internet images such as webcams.
